Fix two quality issues in `web/templates/new.html`.

## Issue 1: Slug generation doesn't strip special characters (line 87)

Current:
```javascript
const slug = nameInput.value.trim().toLowerCase().replace(/\s+/g, '-');
```

Problem: Special characters like `@`, `!`, `(`, `)` remain in the slug, creating invalid filesystem paths.

Fix:
```javascript
const slug = nameInput.value.trim().toLowerCase()
  .replace(/[^a-z0-9\s-]/g, '')  // remove chars that aren't alphanumeric, space, or hyphen
  .replace(/\s+/g, '-')           // spaces → hyphens
  .replace(/-+/g, '-')            // collapse multiple hyphens
  .replace(/^-|-$/g, '');         // trim leading/trailing hyphens
```

## Issue 2: No `res.ok` check before `res.json()` (lines 100-106)

Current:
```javascript
try {
  const res = await fetch('/pick-folder');
  const data = await res.json();
  if (data.path) {
    input.value = data.path;
    if (inputId === 'ws-path') pathManuallyEdited = true;
  }
} catch (_) {
  // Network error — silently ignore, button re-enables below
}
```

Problem: If server returns HTTP 500, `res.json()` may fail or return error JSON, causing silent failure.

Fix:
```javascript
try {
  const res = await fetch('/pick-folder');
  if (!res.ok) return;
  const data = await res.json();
  if (data.path) {
    input.value = data.path;
    if (inputId === 'ws-path') pathManuallyEdited = true;
  }
} catch (_) {
  // Network error — silently ignore, button re-enables below
}
```

## Also fix the btn.textContent whitespace (suggestion, easy fix)

Current (line 96):
```javascript
const originalLabel = btn.textContent;
```

The button's inner text has whitespace from HTML formatting. Use `.trim()`:
```javascript
const originalLabel = btn.textContent.trim();
```

